00:22:00,331 --> 00:22:01,351
Any other councilors have any questions?

254
00:22:03,772 --> 00:22:05,273
Good evening, name and address of the record, please.

255
00:22:08,294 --> 00:22:10,575
Hi, Patricia Daugherty, 235 Winthrop Street.

256
00:22:11,396 --> 00:22:24,701
I'm so glad to see this on the agenda tonight because you may or may not know that since the day after the election, there have been a lot of issues about getting information from the city clerk's office and from the register of voters office.

257
00:22:27,443 --> 00:22:28,363
Did any of you know that?

258
00:22:30,861 --> 00:22:39,826
Well, normally before the election, campaigns can come and get information freely from the city clerk's office or the register of voters office.

259
00:22:40,726 --> 00:22:46,850
And usually after the election, a volunteer will go in and ask for the voter activity list.

260
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:55,034
And so after the September 2nd preliminary, we have got the voter activity list.

261
00:22:55,694 --> 00:23:00,197
And that list is important because it'll allow you to fine tune

262
00:23:01,030 --> 00:23:02,911
the list you'll use in the next mailing.

263
00:23:03,492 --> 00:23:06,354
It tells you who voted, who didn't vote, what parties voted.

264
00:23:06,374 --> 00:23:08,275
Point of information, Vice President Knight.

265
00:23:08,536 --> 00:23:09,056
I noticed, Ms.

266
00:23:09,076 --> 00:23:10,677
Brady, that you said we.

267
00:23:11,158 --> 00:23:13,780
Are you here representing a group or an organization, or are you here as a citizen?

268
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,242
No, I'm saying as volunteers, as like a volunteer.

269
00:23:17,002 --> 00:23:21,385
Do you mean like as a volunteer in general may do this practice?

270
00:23:21,405 --> 00:23:22,066
No, I went in there.

271
00:23:22,206 --> 00:23:25,589
I went in because I had volunteered on several campaigns this fall.

272
00:23:25,669 --> 00:23:27,010
So you're speaking as an individual today.

273
00:23:27,050 --> 00:23:29,852
But at this moment, I'm speaking as me who went in.

274
00:23:30,895 --> 00:23:44,899
So I went in to get, so the day after the November 2nd election, I went in to get the numbers, the unofficial official numbers, and knowing that they are not official until of course they're certified.

275
00:23:45,639 --> 00:23:51,241
And I also asked if I could then, when would the voter activity list for November 2nd be ready?

276
00:23:51,321 --> 00:23:52,361
Usually that's a week or so.

277
00:23:52,381 --> 00:23:54,322
And so they gave a date.

278
00:23:56,582 --> 00:23:58,603
But I also heard when I was down there,

279
00:23:59,441 --> 00:24:14,551
that a list of 12,546 people had been moved from active to inactive back to active again before the preliminary election.

280
00:24:15,431 --> 00:24:16,852
Now, were you people aware of that?

281
00:24:22,476 --> 00:24:24,817
Through the chair, Councilor Mox, you were aware of that?

282
00:24:25,478 --> 00:24:25,718
Correct.

283
00:24:29,580 --> 00:24:40,290
called the Secretary of State's office and Michelle Tassinieri got back to me and she's chief legal counsel, as many of you might know, and she explained what happened.

284
00:24:40,370 --> 00:24:48,298
She said that the city clerk's office had moved 12,546 people to inactive status and

285
00:24:53,187 --> 00:24:56,568
then it, but it was done too close to the next election.

286
00:24:57,188 --> 00:25:05,030
So, and I can't remember whether she said notices were sent out or not sent out because what happens is the city does their annual street listing.

287
00:25:05,090 --> 00:25:10,071
And if you don't respond, you then are removed from the active photo list.

288
00:25:10,911 --> 00:25:16,512
And, but before they do that, they send a card out to remind you that you didn't fill out your street census.

289
00:25:17,593 --> 00:25:19,313
And so when I was talking to her,

290
00:25:20,088 --> 00:25:22,309
She said, but it was too close to the timeline.

291
00:25:22,369 --> 00:25:23,629
Someone had filed a complaint.

292
00:25:24,269 --> 00:25:26,170
And I said, well, how would they know that?

293
00:25:26,530 --> 00:25:30,351
How would they know that there was anything to complain about?

294
00:25:30,431 --> 00:25:34,012
And she said, well, I'm not sure you'd have to find that out from the city clerk's office.

295
00:25:34,812 --> 00:25:40,594
So, but the other thing I asked her about is I said, there are 41,000 people registered to vote in the city.

296
00:25:40,634 --> 00:25:43,534
And the census says we only have 59,000 people.

297
00:25:43,995 --> 00:25:45,315
Doesn't that seem very high to you?

298
00:25:45,395 --> 00:25:46,795
And she said, it seems really high.

299
00:25:47,756 --> 00:25:48,916
And she said, why don't you go back

300
00:25:49,621 --> 00:25:55,924
take out, go to the recent census and take out all the kids, everyone under 18 who can't vote.

301
00:25:56,364 --> 00:26:04,807
And then if you come up with a really high number, then go to your council, go to the registrar's office and suggest that maybe there needs to be some sort of deeper review.

302
00:26:05,868 --> 00:26:09,989
So I did what she said, and we came up with a really high number.

303
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:18,753
And just to make sure it wasn't off base, I took Wellesley, which I knew to be a very high,

304
00:26:19,810 --> 00:26:21,110
owner occupied city.

305
00:26:21,711 --> 00:26:26,832
And I knew they had very high public participation because they have hundreds of people show up at their town meetings.

306
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:29,593
And then I thought, well, this is kind of extreme.

307
00:26:29,633 --> 00:26:31,593
I'll just go next door to Winchester, the same thing.

308
00:26:32,174 --> 00:26:41,816
And so both Wellesley and Winchester have an 80% of their population is registered to vote and they have 90%, give or take, owner occupied.

309
00:26:41,916 --> 00:26:42,997
So you would expect that.

310
00:26:44,697 --> 00:26:46,558
Well, Medford has 85% of our

311
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:50,461
population registered to vote.

312
00:26:51,762 --> 00:26:56,385
And that is extremely high because we're only at 56% owner occupied.

313
00:26:57,586 --> 00:27:06,431
So I'm suggesting that there might want to be some investigation into why our we have such a high number registered to vote in the city.

314
00:27:07,912 --> 00:27:10,354
But the other thing is I said to her, well, if

315
00:27:12,523 --> 00:27:19,288
We were going to delete 12,546 people from the list that would leave 29,000 people registered to vote.

316
00:27:20,228 --> 00:27:26,713
Listen, that seemed like a really high number to delete and she said it is a really high number, she said you need to ask maybe.

317
00:27:27,338 --> 00:27:30,419
the city clerk wasn't deleting the list, cleaning up the list every year.

318
00:27:30,439 --> 00:27:34,101
You know, maybe you go back seven or eight years and they hadn't cleaned up the list.

319
00:27:34,141 --> 00:27:35,581
And I thought, well, that was unusual.

320
00:27:35,641 --> 00:27:36,562
That would be not right.

321
00:27:36,962 --> 00:27:42,024
Well, I happened to run into Ed Finn outside one day and he said, no, we cleaned up the list every year.

322
00:27:42,084 --> 00:27:44,065
And he said, I think Adam has been doing it also.

323
00:27:44,525 --> 00:27:48,326
So I think another question we have to ask is how did we get to 12,546 people on the list?

324
00:27:48,346 --> 00:27:49,247
Maybe that's part of the review.

325
00:27:53,902 --> 00:27:55,543
Well, there were a couple more questions here.

326
00:27:56,124 --> 00:28:03,290
So anyway, I waited the week and I walked back into city clerk's office to see if the voter activity list was ready.

327
00:28:04,190 --> 00:28:06,112
And I was told, we can't talk to you.

328
00:28:06,933 --> 00:28:08,514
I said, me or everybody?

329
00:28:09,174 --> 00:28:10,015
We can't talk to anyone.

330
00:28:10,095 --> 00:28:12,677
And I said, what do you mean you can't talk to anyone?

331
00:28:13,097 --> 00:28:14,999
We can't give out any lists, we can't do anything.

332
00:28:15,019 --> 00:28:17,581
I said, what do you mean?

333
00:28:18,642 --> 00:28:22,325
I was told we could committing, you have the voter activity list, why can't I have it?

334
00:28:23,980 --> 00:28:25,641
And they said, we just can't tell you anything.

335
00:28:26,902 --> 00:28:28,764
I thought, this is really weird.

336
00:28:28,844 --> 00:28:32,447
Like normally you only shut down the flow of communication when there's a criminal investigation.

337
00:28:33,208 --> 00:28:34,709
I said, is there a criminal investigation?

338
00:28:34,729 --> 00:28:35,510
They said, we can't talk.

339
00:28:36,751 --> 00:28:38,372
So I went down the register of voters office.

340
00:28:38,392 --> 00:28:41,875
This is Wednesday, November 10th.

341
00:28:43,196 --> 00:28:45,017
And I said, Sandy Gill was there.

342
00:28:45,057 --> 00:28:49,401
And I said, could I get the list I talked about with you last week?

343
00:28:49,441 --> 00:28:51,823
And she said, I'm sorry, we can't talk to you.

344
00:28:53,198 --> 00:28:55,840
And I said, what are you talking about?

345
00:28:55,860 --> 00:28:57,481
And no one would look up.

346
00:28:57,581 --> 00:28:58,702
Everyone was really nervous.

347
00:28:59,562 --> 00:29:01,083
And it was the weirdest state of affairs.

348
00:29:01,123 --> 00:29:04,945
So I went home, called up seeing Michelle Tassineri again.

349
00:29:04,965 --> 00:29:08,608
And she called me back later on.

350
00:29:08,928 --> 00:29:11,149
And someone said, we can't talk to you.

351
00:29:11,410 --> 00:29:14,031
The Secretary of State's office said we can't talk to anyone right now.

352
00:29:15,332 --> 00:29:16,493
Oh, I forgot one important thing.

353
00:29:16,533 --> 00:29:17,353
So I went upstairs.

354
00:29:17,433 --> 00:29:19,114
They said, you got to go to the city solicitor's office.

355
00:29:19,154 --> 00:29:19,775
So I went there.

356
00:29:20,528 --> 00:29:21,849
And she was too busy to talk to me.

357
00:29:21,889 --> 00:29:25,031
They said, you have to file a freedom of information to get this information.

358
00:29:25,652 --> 00:29:27,473
I said, this is unbelievable.

359
00:29:27,493 --> 00:29:30,476
I said, we just got the exact same list like in September.

360
00:29:31,496 --> 00:29:42,104
So I went to the mayor's office and there was a meeting going on and I got to go in and I said, can you please tell me under what authority are you shutting down the flow of information?

361
00:29:42,164 --> 00:29:44,026
Is there a criminal investigation going on here?

362
00:29:45,402 --> 00:29:49,084
And the mayor didn't answer me.

363
00:29:49,144 --> 00:29:56,248
I understand that there's some emotions running high, but to keep insinuating, is there a criminal investigation?

364
00:29:56,288 --> 00:29:59,430
Is there a criminal investigation?

365
00:29:59,490 --> 00:30:04,633
I'm just thinking that, you know, the narrative is getting a little skewed here.

366
00:30:04,673 --> 00:30:06,354
You know what I mean?

367
00:30:06,414 --> 00:30:07,735
Let's keep it to the facts, please.

368
00:30:07,755 --> 00:30:08,856
That's all I'm saying.

369
00:30:08,936 --> 00:30:11,437
Is there a criminal investigation?

370
00:30:11,497 --> 00:30:11,978
I mean, come on.

371
00:30:12,750 --> 00:30:15,253
That is the question.

372
00:30:15,533 --> 00:30:18,556
That's a very factual statement I made because that's what I said.

373
00:30:19,377 --> 00:30:21,599
I said, how are you shutting down the flow of information?

374
00:30:21,759 --> 00:30:23,401
Is there a criminal investigation going on?

375
00:30:23,461 --> 00:30:26,144
Because normally that's the only time you would shut down the flow of information.

376
00:30:27,125 --> 00:30:30,168
And I was told by the chief of staff answered me, not the mayor.

377
00:30:30,868 --> 00:30:34,272
And she said, you have to go through the city solicitor and file a FOIA.

378
00:30:35,810 --> 00:30:53,154
So I was like, this is- Wait, Mr. President, it was brought to my attention after having a conversation with the elections coordinator that because of the inordinate number of requests that the office was getting relative to the provision of certain documents that they sought advice from the Secretary of State's office as to how to handle it.

379
00:30:53,234 --> 00:30:57,155
And then the Secretary of State's office said these requests can be handled as Freedom of Information Act requests.

380
00:30:58,155 --> 00:30:59,956
So Mr. President, to continue,

381
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:06,263
Michelle Tassinari legal counsel for the Secretary of State's office called me back that afternoon around 430.

382
00:31:08,144 --> 00:31:09,585
And she was very upset.

383
00:31:09,765 --> 00:31:16,029
And she said, I not only called city clerk's office, city hall, she said, I emailed them.

384
00:31:16,910 --> 00:31:23,294
And I told them under no circumstances are they to use our office as the authority in shutting down information.

385
00:31:24,134 --> 00:31:25,535
She said, I don't know why they're doing it.

386
00:31:25,655 --> 00:31:26,856
It's extremely unusual.

387
00:31:27,376 --> 00:31:29,978
She said, but in order for you to get information, you'll have to file.

388
00:31:33,215 --> 00:31:35,537
The next day was Veterans Day, the office was closed.

389
00:31:35,617 --> 00:31:42,080
I went Friday and filed eight or nine requests for the information that is normally given to us.

390
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:50,805
So the questions I'd like to know is, you people hire and fire the city clerk, did you give the order to shut down the information?

391
00:31:50,825 --> 00:31:50,865
No.

392
00:31:56,107 --> 00:32:00,950
So, but the most important question now is,

393
00:32:02,896 --> 00:32:06,318
What is the background on the 12,546 names?

394
00:32:07,219 --> 00:32:11,782
Did you have that information before either the preliminary or the election?

395
00:32:12,783 --> 00:32:16,025
That there was this list that went from active to inactive to active?

396
00:32:16,065 --> 00:32:19,287
Did you- I can't speak for the council.

397
00:32:19,327 --> 00:32:22,369
The Memphis City Council doesn't perform election oversight duties.

398
00:32:22,449 --> 00:32:25,971
That's what the board of registrars vote as far as, and that's what the secretary of state's office as well.

399
00:32:26,412 --> 00:32:27,252
Well, through the chair,

400
00:32:29,137 --> 00:32:55,533
Secretary, Michelle Tosineri said that, that is something that was, so it was a major mistake, but it was a major mistake that should have been brought to the attention of the administration in the city, both council president and the mayor, because it was, it meant that nobody had to go to a voting, to the precincts and show

401
00:32:56,922 --> 00:33:04,170
a license and or sign an affirmation that they lived where they say they lived and they had lived there January 1.

402
00:33:05,612 --> 00:33:16,023
And so did any of you, Councilor Behrs, Councilor Knight, the Councilors over here, did you people know that there was this information of 12,546 names out there?

403
00:33:20,025 --> 00:33:31,588
quite frankly, I don't pay much attention to the functions of the office that falls under the purview of the administration that has a department head and a board that's required to make sure that they're in compliance with what's going on.

404
00:33:31,708 --> 00:33:32,928
It's the city clerk's office.

405
00:33:33,409 --> 00:33:34,889
It's also the board of registrars of voters.

406
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:37,970
Yes, but the city clerk is the city clerk that was the one that was told.

407
00:33:38,050 --> 00:33:42,311
Are you insinuating that the city clerk is conducting some sort of bad behavior or something like that?

408
00:33:42,351 --> 00:33:45,952
Because if that's the case, we're really going down a slippery slope here.

409
00:33:45,992 --> 00:33:47,212
I'm not suggesting any of that.

410
00:33:47,252 --> 00:33:48,153
I'm asking questions.

411
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:49,173
I have questions to ask.

412
00:33:49,698 --> 00:33:58,782
So what Michelle Tosineri, legal counsel, she said these questions should be answered by city hall.

413
00:33:59,342 --> 00:34:02,824
Now, I said the city council hires and fires the city clerk's office.

414
00:34:02,924 --> 00:34:16,730
I don't know what the city clerk knew or didn't know, but she did tell me that he, she had him put the list back, the active that he put on inactive, she had him put it back to active because it was within a timeframe.

415
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:20,966
And she said a citizen had called in to complain to the Secretary of State's office.

416
00:34:21,327 --> 00:34:25,012
And my question to her as well how would anyone know to even call in.

417
00:34:27,048 --> 00:34:32,753
And to do that, like in the different campaigns that people were out there, they didn't have this list.

418
00:34:33,133 --> 00:34:42,341
And if you knew the list existed or the information existed, it would be something that you would wanna get just like the way you go in and get the voter activity list from September 2nd.

419
00:34:42,381 --> 00:34:50,788
All right, well, I just have the questions I'd like answered is who gave the authority in city hall and under what authority did they have to shut down the information?

420
00:34:51,969 --> 00:34:55,292
And then the other thing is- I don't think anybody in this room has that answer.

421
00:34:56,678 --> 00:34:58,118
And I just want to be clear.

422
00:34:58,318 --> 00:35:02,780
So you did say that the Secretary of State's office did say to put these inactive voters back onto the active voters.

423
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:03,260
Yes.

424
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:15,443
And then, but, but I don't so as of today we still, I do know that one person who requested the information did get was sent had the list.

425
00:35:16,772 --> 00:35:18,073
I have not been sent the list.

426
00:35:18,213 --> 00:35:22,856
And now I know that city clerk's office, they have COVID and maybe they're all out sick with it and they can't do that.

427
00:35:22,896 --> 00:35:23,816
Maybe that's the answer.

428
00:35:24,337 --> 00:35:29,059
But it is very discouraging to know that anything that you normally would get, you cannot get right now.

429
00:35:29,780 --> 00:35:30,120
Thank you.

430
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:31,961
The city clerk's office isn't the keeper of the records.

431
00:35:32,101 --> 00:35:34,142
